#eNCA's Tshegohaco Moagi and Nqobile Madlala have more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Self-proclaimed Prophet Shepherd Bushiri, his wife Mary, and three others will return to court on Monday for a bail hearing. The five appeared in court on Friday and the matter was postponed until Monday. They have been in custody for almost two weeks. READ: Bushiri couple to spend another weekend behind bars They are facing charges of fraud, theft, and money laundering to the value of over R100-million. The State says the accused will abscond if they are granted bail.